\begin_layout Standard
Public sector output consists of all the different goods and services provided
 by the state, from education and health care, to the judicial system and
 defense, and to child care, elderly care, etc.
 This output, 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{G}$
\end_inset

, is not exported.
 It is entirely consumed domestically.
 The vast majority of these services are paid for using tax revenues or
 using the intake from public debt issues.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A small share of public services are paid directly by private agents, as
 is the case for some co-payments for health care and education.
 These private payments are included in household consumption of services
 and we denote this private consumption of government supplied services
 as 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{t}^{\text{Pub}}$
\end_inset

.
 The government also makes direct investments, 
\begin_inset Formula $I_{t}^{\text{Pub}}$
\end_inset

, which is almost entirely publicly funded R&D and accounted for as a public
 production of investments in equipment
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

